node.text: How can you tell, when you’re always turned on? Introducing... The Gentle Giant💡the latest member of our lighting collection and the beguiling star of ‘The Moth’. This short film was written and directed by my talented friend @geordieleyland, with a beautiful score written for us by @_rocheman. The simple brief I gave Geordie morphed into something much stranger and larger scale than I had in mind. It was pretty surreal standing on a set with my husband dressed head to toe in moth gear with 20 other moth extras and a full crew and cameras! Anyway, I hope this little love story will bring a smile to your face... If you do like it, it would be wonderful if you feel like sharing it! For those looking for a new wall lantern that can go on the inside or outside of your home, The Gentle Giant is available now on our Shoppa (link in bio)😊

node.text: It was a joy to work with @therugcompany on this beautifully made mermaid rug for Gurli & Alma’s playroom 🧜🏻‍♀️🌊 Inspired by one of Marlon Brando’s tattoos, this will hopefully be a piece the girls will treasure & remember fondly in years to come 🐟

node.text:
Entry hall looking into living space, the Stig Lindberg wall hanging makes it come alive! The table, which was inspired by a vintage piece, was built bespoke to fit around the radiator and with little drawers for keys etc... 

📸 @simonbrownphotography styling @studio_cruz 

#interiordesign #interiors #insipration #inredning #beataheuman #beataheumaninteriors

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Beata Heuman in London, United Kingdom with @beataheuman. May be an image of living room.

node.text:
Looking from the main bedroom to the dressing room (with bath) which is covered in our Florentine Flowers wallpaper. It was the very first time we used it! We made the eiderdown on the bed bespoke , inspired but one I saw in a 1920s pin-up photograph 🤫. The house itself is the most wonderful London property from the turn of the last century- wish it was my own tbh ❤️. 

📸 @simonbrownphotography 

#interiors #beataheumaninteriors #beataheuman #bedroom #design #inredning #inspiration

node.text:
A recently completed bathroom in London. I never tire of these kind of tones of bluey greens and whites. The cipollino marble looks like an underwater landscape! 

📸 @simonbrownphotography 

#bathroom #london #badrum #insipration #interiors #inredning #beataheuman #beataheumaninteriors

node.text: I had a wonderful time visiting Tina @theapartmentdk in Copenhagen! The beautiful space is filled to the brim with inspiring vintage designs and a few new pieces by some of my favourites such as @nathaliefarmanfarma , @malaikalinens and @campbellrey ❤️. Thank you so much for having me Tina!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Beata Heuman in London, United Kingdom with @beataheuman. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
A children’s bathroom in Notting Hill. The floor tiles are reclaimed, and the Zellige tiles around the bath and walls were painstakingly installed by our tiler without (much) complaining. Our Aslan stool is covered in a towel slip cover - like a wolf in sheep’s clothing. If you lift the skirt you’ll see some devilishly red lion paw feet... 

#bathroom #interiordesign #interiors #beataheuman #beataheumaninteriors

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Beata Heuman in Piren Borstahusen. May be an image of 3 people, child, people sitting, people standing and outdoors.

node.text: Me and the girls taken by John. We’re about to take a dip in the sea in Borstahusen, a short drive from my parent’s farm. I’m so excited to show them some Swedish countryside living - the girls absolutely love it too, especially as their mother has done a 180 when it comes to nutrition. Apparently anything goes if it has nostalgic connotations 😬....

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Beata Heuman on July 12, 2021 tagging @beataheuman. May be an illustration of text.

node.text:
Introducing the Moon! A calming presence that casts a beautifully diffused light and works particularly well in rooms when seen a lot from underneath such as in a bedroom. The shade is made by a small workshop in Rome using a fine ivory wool for the exterior of the shade and a cotton poplin for the interior. The solid brass neoclassical rosette is hand-painted and waxed and bares our signature green, as does the twisted flex. In stock ready to be shipped worldwide 💫. 

#themoon #interiordesign #pendant #beataheuman #beataheumaninteriors

node.text:
A detail of a drawing room in a project we completed last year. This home came together over just 6 months and was one of our quickest ever turn arounds, but it’s also one of my favourites. The Paula Rego lithograph was always intended for this wall and it was a really exciting moment when it was hung - it all came together just as we envisaged it! 

📸 @simonbrownphotography styling @studio_cruz 

#interiors #interiordesign #livingroom #vardagsrum #beataheuman #beataheumaninteriors

node.text:
A small kitchen in London, a project I worked on with @foscamariani . The kitchen is kind of Swedish Funkis style, which I think works really well with the early Victorian cornicing. The building is Grade II listed which meant there were all sorts of restrictions such as not moving the picture rail. We stopped the top cupboards at the same height and added some decorative plates above to draw the gaze upwards and make the most of the amazing ceiling heights. 

📸 @simonbrownphotography #interior #interiordesign #kitchen #kök #inspiration #londonkitchen #beataheuman #beataheumaninteriors

node.text: I’m honoured to be featured on the cover of Salon’s summer issue! Thank you so much @anne_petersen @salon_magazin . The feature showcases my inspiration and work, particularly in relation to my book, making it a part of the new “sketchbook” series in the magazine... ‘Every room should sing’ is now also back in stock on Shoppa, just follow link in Bio. Now off to go and find myself a German translator... 😂

node.text:
London entry - simple and quite narrow as they often are, but the mirror adds depth, and the velvet covered table top is a place to put your keys and post. The Constance Spry vase was the perfect shape - maximum shape - minimum depth. The brass doors were reclaimed from the BBC Television centre - which was my client’s brilliant idea! 

I love this picture by @simonbrownphotography ...

A study on a stair landing, I love the enormous window adding to the theatre of it all - with my favourite @nickyphaslam shutter stripe on the blind and @nathaliefarmanfarma fabric for the cushion on the desk chair from @soanebritain . We designed the desk for the space.
